            <div><div class="cbl">// Problem</div><p class="cbt">An AI data operations program for a Fortune 10 client was producing inconsistent evaluation quality — recurring annotation errors, no unified SLA visibility, and unclear root causes across a distributed team.</p></div>
            <div><div class="cbl">// Context</div><p class="cbt">Training data quality determines how AI models perform in real products. A systematic gap between what was annotated and what was correct meant downstream AI — voice recognition, handwriting detection, predictive text — would be unreliable at scale for millions of users.</p></div>
